8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 351, L.D. 532, “An Act to Protect Health
10 Care Workers by Addressing Assaults in Health Care Settings”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'Resolve, to Study Assaults on Health Care Workers'
13 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the title and inserting the following:
14 'Sec. 1. Commissioner of Health and Human Services to convene working
15 group. Resolved: That the Commissioner of Health and Human Services shall convene
16 a working group to study assaults on health care workers in health care facilities.
17 Sec. 2. Membership. Resolved: That the working group convened under section
18 1 must include, but is not limited to, the following members:
19 1. The Commissioner of Health and Human Services or the commissioner's designee;
20 2. A representative of a statewide association representing hospitals;
21 3. A representative of a statewide organization representing entities that provide long-
22 term care services;
23 4. A representative of a statewide organization representing entities that provide
24 outpatient care services;
25 5. A representative of a statewide organization representing entities that provide mental
26 health services;
27 6. A representative of a statewide association representing prosecutors;
28 7. A representative of a statewide association representing criminal defense lawyers;
29 8. A representative of a statewide association representing law enforcement officers;
30 and
31 9. A representative of a statewide organization representing health care workers.
Page 1 - 132LR1158(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 351, L.D. 532
1 Sec. 3. Duties of working group. Resolved: That the working group convened
2 under section 1 must include the following topics in its study:
3 1. A review of current data on assaults on health care workers in health care facilities
4 in the State;
5 2. Current efforts by health care entities to prevent assaults on health care workers; and
6 3. Best practices to deter assaults on health care workers.
7 Sec. 4. Report. Resolved: That, by January 1, 2026, the Commissioner of Health
8 and Human Services shall submit a report containing the findings and recommendations of
9 the working group under section 1, including proposed legislation, to the Joint Standing
10 Committee on Criminal Justice and Public Safety and the Joint Standing Committee on
11 Health and Human Services. The Joint Standing Committee on Criminal Justice and Public
12 Safety may report out legislation based on the report to the Second Regular Session of the
13 132nd Legislature.'
14 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
15 number to read consecutively.
16 SUMMARY
1177 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, replaces the bill with
1188 a resolve. The amendment directs the Commissioner of Health and Human Services to
1199 convene a working group to study assaults on health care workers in health care facilities.
2200 The commissioner is required to submit a report by January 1, 2026 to the Joint Standing
2211 Committee on Criminal Justice and Public Safety and the Joint Standing Committee on
2222 Health and Human Services. The Joint Standing Committee on Criminal Justice and Public
2233 Safety may report out legislation based on the report to the Second Regular Session of the
2244 132nd Legislature.
2255 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
2266 (See attached)
